main event: A well-known aerodynamist reported an incident in mid-December 195[obscured] in northern Arizona, along Route 66, involving a high-speed, unidentified flying object at an altitude of 20,000 to 50,000 feet, traveling at 600 mph from east to west. The object left behind a thick, heavy trail, but the observer did not see the actual object.
interesting points: The observer was a well-known aerodynamist from the University of Colorado, Boulder, adding credibility to the sighting.
The sighting took place in the early morning in clear weather conditions, indicating good visibility.
The UFO was observed traveling at a high speed of 600 mph and at a high altitude of 20,000 to 50,000 feet.
The thick, heavy trail left by the object differed from a regular vapor trail, suggesting unusual propulsion or emissions.
Despite not seeing the actual object, the observer noted the trail left by the UFO, providing some evidence of its presence.
sighted object: unidentified flying object leaving behind a thick, heavy trail
witnesses: aerodynamist from the University of Colorado, Boulder
